OpenFlow.NBAPI
Class SwitchInfo

java.lang.Object
  OpenFlow.NBAPI.SwitchInfo
Direct Known Subclasses:
SwitchInfoList.MySwitchInfo
public class SwitchInfo
extends java.lang.Object

Collection of information regarding a datapathID for a managed switch.

Overrides hashCode() and equals(Object) to be suitable for use with utility classes in the java.util package. Entries may be marked as "locked" against automatic removal by a SwitchInfoList.clearUnlocked() call.

Convert to String with specified port entry separator.

Set this entry's "locked" state.

isIgnored

public boolean isIgnored()
Get this entry's "ignored" state.

setIgnored

public void setIgnored(boolean ignored)
Set this entry's "ignored" state.

If ignored is true, this entry will not be included in a containing list's SwitchInfoList.dup() call. When used on entries owned by a ControllerContext, allows for the entry to be excluded from any default operations on all managed switches (without having to continually remove the entry when the server provides updated switch information).
